obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32931)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32931&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Black Money`
  line `(Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets) and Imposition of Tax Act, 2015.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, it shall come into force on the 1st day of April, 2016.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32932)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32932&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(1) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 252 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(2) "assessee" means a person, being a resident other than not ordinarily resident in India within`
  line `the meaning of clause (6) of section 6 of the Income-tax Act, by whom tax in respect of undisclosed`
  line `foreign income and assets, or any other sum of money, is payable under this Act and includes every`
  line `person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under this Act;`
  line
  line `(3) "assessment" includes reassessment;`
  line
  line `(4) "assessment year" means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April`
  line `every year;`
  line
  line `(5) "Board" means the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(6) 'Income-tax Act" means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(7) "participant" means—`
  line
  line `(a) a partner in relation to a firm; or`
  line
  line `(b) a member in relation to an association of persons or body of individuals;`
  line
  line `(8) "prescribed' means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(9) "previous year" means—`
  line
  line `(a) the period beginning with the date of setting up of a business and ending with the date of`
  line `the closure of the business or the 31st day of March following the date of setting up of such`
  line `business, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(b) the period beginning with the date on which a new source of income comes into existence`
  line `and ending with the date of closure of the business or the 31st day of March following the date on`
  line `which such new source comes into existence, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(c) the period beginning with the 1st day of the financial year and ending with the date of`
  line `discontinuance of the business other than business referred to in clause (b) or dissolution of an`
  line `unincorporated body or liquidation of a company, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(d) the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April of the relevant year in`
  line `any other case,`
  line
  line `and which immediately precedes the assessment year.`
  line
  line `(10) "resident" means a person who is resident in India within the meaning of Section 6 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(11) "undisclosed asset located outside India" means an asset (including financial interest in any`
  line `entity) located outside India, held by the assessee in his name or in respect of which he is a beneficial`
  line `owner, and he has no explanation about the source of investment in such asset or the explanation`
  line `given by him is in the opinion of the Assessing Officer unsatisfactory;`
  line
  line `(12) "undisclosed foreign income and asset" means the total amount of undisclosed income of an`
  line `assessee from a source located outside India and the value of an undisclosed asset located outside`
  line `India, referred to in section 4, and computed in the manner laid down in Section 5;`
  line
  line `(13) "unincorporated body" means—`
  line
  line `(a) a firm;`
  line
  line `(b) an association of persons; or`
  line
  line `(c) a body of individuals;`
  line
  line `(14) "value of an undisclosed asset" shall have the meaning assigned to it in sub-section (2) of`
  line `Section 3;`
  line
  line `(15) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Income-tax`
  line `Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32933)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Charge of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32933&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be charged on every assessee for every assessment year`
  line `commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2016, subject to the provisions of this Act, a tax in respect of`
  line `his total undisclosed foreign income and asset of the previous year at the rate of thirty per cent. of such`
  line `undisclosed income and asset:`
  line
  line `Provided that an undisclosed asset located outside India shall be charged to tax on its value in the`
  line `previous year in which such asset comes to the notice of the Assessing Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, "value of an undisclosed asset" means the fair market value of an`
  line `asset (including financial interest in any entity) determined in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32934)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Scope of total undisclosed foreign income and asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32934&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the total undisclosed foreign income and asset of any previous year of an assessee shall be,—`
  line
  line `(a) the income from a source located outside India, which has not been disclosed in the return of`
  line `income furnished within the time specified in Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) or under`
  line `sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) of section 139 of the Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the income, from a source located outside India, in respect of which a return is required to be`
  line `furnished under section 139 of the Income-tax Act but no return of income has been furnished within`
  line `the time specified in Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) or under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 139 of the said Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) the value of an undisclosed asset located outside India.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any variation made in the income from a`
  line `source outside India in the assessment or reassessment of the total income of any previous year, of the`
  line `assessee under the Income-tax Act in accordance with the provisions of section 29 to section 43C or`
  line `section 57 to section 59 or section 92C of the said Act, shall not be included in the total undisclosed`
  line `foreign income.`
  line
  line `(3) The income included in the total undisclosed foreign income and asset under this Act shall not`
  line `form part of the total income under the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32935)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Computation of total undisclosed foreign income and asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32935&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the total`
  line `undisclosed foreign income and asset of any previous year of an assessee,—`
  line
  line `(i) no deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance or set off of any loss shall be allowed`
  line `to the assessee, whether or not it is allowable in accordance with the provisions of the Income-tax`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(ii) any income,—`
  line
  line `(a) which has been assessed to tax for any assessment year under the Income-tax Act prior to`
  line `the assessment year to which this Act applies; or`
  line
  line `(b) which is assessable or has been assessed to tax for any assessment year under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be reduced from the value of the undisclosed asset located outside India, if, the assessee furnishes`
  line `evidence to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer that the asset has been acquired from the income`
  line `which has been assessed or is assessable, as the case may be, to tax.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of deduction referred to in clause (ii) of sub-section (1) in case of an immovable`
  line `property shall be the amount which bears to the value of the asset as on the first day of the financial year`
  line `in which it comes to the notice of the Assessing Officer, the same proportion as the assessable or assessed`
  line `foreign income bears to the total cost of the asset.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A house property located outside India was acquired by an assessee in the previous year 2009-10 for`
  line `fifty lakh rupees. Out of the investment of fifty lakh rupees, twenty lakh rupees was assessed to tax in the`
  line `total income of the previous year 2009-10 and earlier years. Such undisclosed asset comes to the notice of`
  line `the Assessing Officer in the year2017-18. If the value of the asset in the year 2017-18 is one crore rupees,`
  line `the amount chargeable to tax shall be A-B= C`
  line
  line where,
  line
  line `A = Rs.1 crore, B = Rs. (100 � 20/50) lakh = Rs.40 lakh, C = Rs. (100-40) lakh = Rs.60 lakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32936)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32936&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The income-tax authorities specified in Section 116 of the Income-tax Act`
  line `shall be the tax authorities for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such authority shall exercise the powers and perform the functions of a tax authority under`
  line `this Act in respect of any person within his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the jurisdiction of a tax authority under this Act shall`
  line `be the same as he has under the Income-tax Act by virtue of orders or directions issued under section 120`
  line `of that Act (including orders or directions assigning the concurrent jurisdiction) or under any other`
  line `provision of that Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The tax authority having jurisdiction in relation to an assessee who has no income assessable to`
  line `income-tax under the Income-tax Act shall be the tax authority having jurisdiction in respect of the area in`
  line `which the assessee resides or carries on its business or has its principal place of business.`
  line
  line `(5) Section 118 of the Income-tax Act and any notification issued thereunder shall apply in relation to`
  line `the control of tax authorities as they apply in relation to the control of the corresponding income-tax`
  line `authorities, except to the extent to which the Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise`
  line `direct in respect of any tax authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32937)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Change of incumbent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32937&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tax authority who succeeds another authority as a result of`
  line `change in jurisdiction or for any other reason, shall continue the proceedings from the stage at which it`
  line `was left by his predecessor.`
  line
  line `(2) The assessee in such a case may be given an opportunity of being heard, if he so requests in`
  line `writing, before passing any order in his case.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32938)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers regarding discovery and production of evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32938&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prescribed tax authorities`
  line `shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) discovery and inspection;`
  line
  line `(b) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a banking company and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(c) compelling the production of books of account and other documents; and`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of making any inquiry or investigation, the prescribed tax authority shall be`
  line `vested with the powers referred to in sub-section (1), whether or not any proceedings are pending before`
  line it.
  line
  line `(3) Any tax authority prescribed for the purposes of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may, subject to`
  line `the rules made in this behalf, impound any books of account or other documents produced before it and`
  line `retain them in its custody for such period as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Any tax authority below the rank of Commissioner shall not—`
  line
  line `(a) impound any books of account or other documents without recording his reasons for doing so;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) retain in his custody any such books or documents for a period exceeding thirty days without`
  line `obtaining the approval of the Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the`
  line `Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32939)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Proceedings before tax authorities to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32939&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any proceeding under this`
  line `Act before a tax authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of section 193`
  line `and section 228 and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Every tax authority shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195, but not for`
  line `the purposes of Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32940)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32940&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of making an assessment or reassessment under this Act, the`
  line `Assessing Officer may, on receipt of an information from an income-tax authority under the Income-tax`
  line `Act or any other authority under any law for the time being in force or on coming of any information to`
  line `his notice, serve on any person, a notice requiring him on a date to be specified to produce or cause to be`
  line `produced such accounts or documents or evidence as the Assessing Officer may require for the purposes`
  line `of this Act and may, from time to time, serve further notices requiring the production of such other`
  line `accounts or documents or evidence as he may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Assessing Officer may make such inquiry, as he considers necessary, for the purpose of`
  line `obtaining full information in respect of undisclosed foreign income and asset of any person for the`
  line `relevant financial year or years.`
  line
  line `(3) The Assessing Officer, after considering such accounts, documents or evidence, as he has`
  line `obtained under sub-section (1), and after taking into account any relevant material which he has gathered`
  line `under sub-section (2) and any other evidence produced by the assessee, shall by an order in writing,`
  line `assess the undisclosed foreign income and asset and determine the sum payable by the assessee.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person fails to comply with all the terms of the notice under sub-section (1), the Assessing`
  line `Officer shall, after taking into account all the relevant material which he has gathered and after giving the`
  line `assessee an opportunity of being heard, make the assessment of undisclosed foreign income and asset to`
  line `the best of his judgment and determine the sum payable by the assessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32941)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Time limit for completion of assessment and reassessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32941&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order of assessment or`
  line `reassessment shall be made under section 10 after the expiry of two years from the end of the financial`
  line `year in which the notice under sub-section (1) of section 10 was issued by the Assessing Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an order of fresh assessment in pursuance`
  line `of an order passed under section 18 setting aside or cancelling an assessment, may be made at any time`
  line `before the expiry of the period of two years from the end of the financial year in which the order under`
  line `section 18 is received by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to the assessment or reassessment made in`
  line `consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in an order under section 15 or`
  line `section 18 or section 19 or section 22 of this Act or in an order of any court in a proceeding otherwise`
  line `than by way of appeal under this Act and such assessment or reassessment may, subject to the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (2), be completed at any time, before the expiry of the period of two years from the end of`
  line `the financial year in which such order is received by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—In computing the period of limitation for the purpose of this section—`
  line
  line `(i) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line `court; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the period commencing from the date on which a reference or first of the references for`
  line `exchange of information is made by an authority competent under an agreement referred to in section`
  line `90 or section 90A of the Income-tax Act or under section 73 of this Act and ending with the date on`
  line `which the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner last receives, the information so requested or`
  line `a period of one year, whichever is less, shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid time or period, the period of`
  line `limitation referred to in sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) available to the Assessing Officer for making an`
  line `order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be, is less than sixty days, such remaining period`
  line `shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—Where, by an order referred to in sub-section (3), any undisclosed foreign income`
  line `and asset is excluded from the total undisclosed foreign income and asset for an assessment year in`
  line `respect of an assessee, then, an assessment of such undisclosed foreign income and asset for another`
  line `assessment year shall, for the purposes of section 10 and this section, be deemed to be one made in`
  line `consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in the said order.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32942)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rectification of mistake.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32942&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tax authority may amend any order passed by it under this Act`
  line `so as to rectify any mistake apparent from the record.`
  line
  line `(2) No amendment under this section shall be made after a period of four years from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be amended was passed.`
  line
  line `(3) The tax authority shall not make any amendment, which has the effect of enhancing the`
  line `undisclosed foreign income and asset or reducing a refund or otherwise increasing the liability of the`
  line `assessee, unless the authority concerned has given to the assessee an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The tax authority concerned may make an amendment under this section—`
  line
  line `(a) on its own motion; or`
  line
  line `(b) on an application made to it by the assessee or, as the case may be, by the Assessing Officer.`
  line
  line `(5) Any application received by the tax authority for amendment of an order shall be decided within a`
  line `period of six months from the end of the month in which such application is received by it.`
  line
  line `(6) In a case where the order has been made in an appeal or revision, the power of the tax authority to`
  line `amend the order shall be restricted to matters other than those decided in appeal or revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32943)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32943&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any sum payable in consequence of any order made under this Act shall be`
  line `demanded by a tax authority by serving upon the assessee a notice of demand in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32944)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Direct assessment or recovery not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32944&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall prevent either the`
  line `direct assessment of the person on whose behalf or for whose benefit the undisclosed income from a`
  line `source located outside India is receivable or undisclosed asset located outside India is held, or the`
  line `recovery from such person of the tax or any other sum of money payable in respect of such income and`
  line asset.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32945)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appeals to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32945&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person,—`
  line
  line `(a) objecting to the amount of tax on undisclosed foreign income and asset for which he is assessed`
  line `by the Assessing Officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) denying his liability to be assessed under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Assessing Officer; or`
  line
  line `(d) objecting to an order of rectification having the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing`
  line `the refund; or`
  line
  line `(e) objecting to an order refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee for a rectification under`
  line `section 12, may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal shall be filed in such form and verified in such manner and be accompanied by a fee`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall be presented within a period of thirty days from—`
  line
  line `(a) the date of service of the notice of demand relating to the assessment or penalty, or`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which the intimation of the order sought to be appealed against is served in any`
  line `other case.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner (Appeals) may admit an appeal after the expiration of the period referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3)—`
  line
  line `(a) if he is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the delay in preferring the appeal does not exceed a period of one year.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall hear and determine the appeal and, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, pass such orders as he thinks fit and such orders may include an order enhancing the assessment`
  line `or penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall not be made unless the assessee has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32946)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure to be followed in appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32946&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall fix a date and`
  line `place for the hearing of the appeal, and shall give notice of the same to the appellant and the Assessing`
  line `Officer against whose order the appeal is preferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The following shall have the right to be heard at the hearing of the appeal, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the appellant, either in person or by an authorised representative;`
  line
  line `(b) the Assessing Officer, either in person or by a representative.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner (Appeals) may adjourn the hearing of the appeal whenever he considers it`
  line `necessary or expedient to do so.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, before disposing of any appeal, make such further inquiry as`
  line `he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, during the proceedings before him, direct the Assessing`
  line `Officer to make an inquiry and report to him on the points arising out of any question of law or fact.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, at the hearing of an appeal, allow the appellant to go into any`
  line `ground of appeal not specified in the grounds of appeal, if the Commissioner (Appeals) is satisfied that`
  line `the omission was not wilful or unreasonable.`
  line
  line `(7) The order of the Commissioner (Appeals) disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall`
  line `state the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(8) Every appeal preferred under section 15 shall be heard and disposed of by the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made to dispose of such appeal within a`
  line `period of one year from the end of the financial year in which the appeal is preferred.`
  line
  line `(9) On the disposal of the appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals) shall communicate the order passed by`
  line `him to the assessee and to the Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32947)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers of Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32947&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) In disposing of an appeal, the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) shall have the following powers, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal against an order of assessment, he may confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the`
  line assessment;
  line
  line `(b) in an appeal against an order imposing a penalty, he may confirm or cancel such order;`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, he may determine the issues arising in the appeal and pass such orders`
  line `thereon, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner (Appeals) may consider and decide any matter which was not considered by`
  line `the Assessing Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall not enhance an assessment or a penalty unless the appellant`
  line `has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) In disposing of an appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals) may consider and decide any matter`
  line `arising out of the proceedings in which the order appealed against was passed, notwithstanding that such`
  line `matter was not raised before him by the appellant.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32948)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32948&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee aggrieved by an order passed by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) under section 15, or an order passed by the Principal Commissioner or the`
  line `Commissioner under any provision of this Act, may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may, if he objects to any order passed by the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) under any provision of this Act, direct the Assessing Officer to appeal to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal against the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be filed within a period of sixty days`
  line `from the date on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the assessee or to the`
  line `Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The Assessing Officer or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) has been preferred under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) by the other party may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order`
  line `or any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections,`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), and such`
  line `memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of crossobjections after the expiry of the period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if —`
  line
  line `(a) it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period; and`
  line
  line `(b) the delay in filing the appeal does not exceed a period of one year.`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be filed in such form, and verified in such manner, and`
  line `shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) or a memorandum of cross-objections`
  line `referred to in sub-section (4), be accompanied by a fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, in hearing and making an order on any appeal under this`
  line `section, the Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the same powers and follow the procedure as it exercises`
  line `and follows in hearing and making an order on any appeal under the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32949)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32949&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie to the High Court from every order passed in`
  line `appeal by the Appellate Tribunal, if the High Court is satisfied that the case involves a substantial`
  line `question of law.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner or`
  line `the Commissioner or an assessee, may file an appeal to the High Court on being aggrieved by any order`
  line `passed by the Appellate Tribunal and such appeal shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) filed within a period of one hundred and twenty days from the date on which the order`
  line `appealed against is received by the Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the`
  line `Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner or the assessee;`
  line
  line `(b) in the form of a memorandum of appeal precisely stating therein the substantial question of`
  line `law involved.`
  line
  line `(3) The High Court may admit an appeal after the expiry of the period of one hundred and twenty`
  line `days referred to in sub-section (2), if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing the appeal`
  line `within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) If the High Court is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any case, it shall`
  line `formulate that question.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal shall be heard only on the question so formulated, and the respondents shall, at the`
  line `hearing of the appeal, be allowed to argue that the case does not involve such question.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything in sub-sections (4) and (5), the High Court may exercise its power to`
  line `hear the appeal on any other substantial question of law not formulated by it, if it is satisfied that the case`
  line `involves such question of law.`
  line
  line `(7) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver such judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and may award such cost as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(8) The High Court may determine any issue which —`
  line
  line `(a) has not been determined by the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been wrongly determined by the Appellate Tribunal, by reason of a decision on the`
  line `question of law referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the High`
  line `Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under this section.`
  line
  line `(10) When the High Court delivers a judgment in an appeal filed before it under sub-section (7),`
  line `effect shall be given to the order passed on the appeal by the Assessing Officer on the basis of a certified`
  line `copy of the judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32950)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Case before High Court to be heard by not less than two Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32950&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal filed before`
  line `the High Court shall be heard by a Bench of not less than two Judges of the High Court and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such Judges or if the Bench is of more than two Judges, by the`
  line `majority of such Judges.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is no such majority, the Judges shall state the point of law upon which they differ and`
  line `the case shall then be heard upon that point only by one or more of the other Judges of the High Court and`
  line `such point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Judges who have heard the`
  line `case including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32951)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32951&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from any judgment of the`
  line `High Court delivered under section 19 which the High Court certifies to be a fit case for appeal to the`
  line `Supreme Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32952)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Hearing before Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32952&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the Supreme Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals`
  line `under section 21 as they apply in the case of appeals from decrees of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The costs of the appeal shall be in the discretion of the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed in the appeal, effect shall be given to`
  line `the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in sub-section (10) of section 19.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32953)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Revision of orders prejudicial to revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32953&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Principal Commissioner or the`
  line `Commissioner may, for the purposes of revising any order passed in any proceeding under this Act before`
  line `any tax authority subordinate to him, call for and examine all available records relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may, after giving the assessee an opportunity of`
  line `being heard, pass an order (hereinafter referred to as the revision order) as the circumstances of the case`
  line `justify, if he is satisfied that the order sought to be revised is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of the revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may make, or cause to be made, such inquiry`
  line `as he considers necessary for the purposes of passing an order under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The revision order passed by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section (2) may have the effect of enhancing or modifying the assessment but shall not be an order`
  line `cancelling the assessment and directing a fresh assessment.`
  line
  line `(5) The power of the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner under sub-section (2) for revising`
  line `an order shall extend to such matters as have not been considered and decided in any appeal.`
  line
  line `(6) No order under sub-section (2) shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `end of the financial year in which the order sought to be revised was passed.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (6), an order in revision under this section may be passed`
  line `at any time in respect of an order which has been passed in consequence of, or to give effect to, any`
  line `finding or direction contained in an order of the Appellate Tribunal, the High Court or the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(8) In computing the period of limitation under sub-section (6), the following shall not be included,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) any period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction`
  line `of any court.`
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, an order passed by a tax authority`
  line `shall be deemed to be erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of the revenue, if in the`
  line `opinion of the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner—`
  line
  line `(a) the order is passed without making inquiries or verification which, should have been made; or`
  line
  line `(b) the order has not been made in accordance with any order, direction or instruction issued by`
  line `the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) the order has not been passed in accordance with any decision, prejudicial to the assessee,`
  line `rendered by the jurisdictional High Court or the Supreme Court in the case of the assessee or any`
  line `other person under this Act or the Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `(10) In this section, "record" shall include all records relating to any proceeding under this Act`
  line `available at the time of examination by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32954)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Revision of other orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32954&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may, either`
  line `suo-motu or on an application made by the assessee, for the purposes of revising any order passed by an`
  line `authority subordinate to him, other than an order to which section 23 applies, call for and examine all`
  line `available records relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may pass an order, as he considers necessary,`
  line `which is not prejudicial to the assessee.`
  line
  line `(3) The power of the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner under sub-section (2) to revise an`
  line `order shall not extend to such order—`
  line
  line `(a) against which an appeal has not been filed but the time for filing an appeal before the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) has not expired;`
  line
  line `(b) against which an appeal is pending before the Commissioner (Appeals); or`
  line
  line `(c) which has been considered and decided in any appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) The assessee shall make the application for revision of any order referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `within a period of one year from the date on which the order sought to be revised was communicated to`
  line `him, or the date on which he otherwise came to know of it, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(5) The Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner may, if he is satisfied that the assessee was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from making the application within the period of one year, admit an`
  line `application made after the expiry of one year but before expiry of two years from the date referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) Every application by an assessee for revision under this section shall be accompanied by such fees`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) No order under sub-section (2) shall be made after the expiry of—`
  line
  line `(a) a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which an application is made by the`
  line `assessee under sub-section (4); or`
  line
  line `(b) a period of one year from the date of the order sought to be revised, if the order is revised`
  line `suo-motu by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(8) In computing the period of limitation under sub-section (7), the following shall not be included,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) any period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction`
  line `of any court.`
  line
  line `(9) An order by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner declining to interfere shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this section, be deemed not to be an order prejudicial to the assessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32955)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Tax to be paid pending appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32955&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any appeal preferred to the High Court or the`
  line `Supreme Court, the tax shall be paid in accordance with the assessment made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32956)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Execution of order for costs awarded by Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32956&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, on petition`
  line `made for the execution of the order in respect of the costs awarded by the Supreme Court, transmit such`
  line `order for execution to any court subordinate to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32957)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of assessment on appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32957&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where as a result of an appeal under section 15 or`
  line `section 18, any change is made in the assessment of a body of individuals or an association of persons or`
  line `an order for new assessment of a body of individuals or an association of persons is made, the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall pass an order authorising the`
  line `Assessing Officer either to amend the assessment made or make a fresh assessment on any member of the`
  line `body or association.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32958)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Exclusion of time taken for obtaining copy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32958&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In computing the period of limitation prescribed`
  line `for an appeal under this Act, the day on which the notice of the order was served upon the assessee`
  line `without serving a copy of the order, the time taken for obtaining a copy of such order, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32959)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Filing of appeal by tax authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32959&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, from time to time, issue orders,`
  line `instructions or directions to other tax authorities, fixing such monetary limits as it may deem fit, for the`
  line `purpose of regulating the filing of appeal by any tax authority under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in pursuance of the orders, instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1), a tax`
  line `authority has not filed any appeal on any issue in the case of an assessee for any financial year, it shall not`
  line `preclude such authority from filing an appeal on the same issue in the case of—`
  line
  line `(a) the same assessee for any other financial year; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other assessee for the same or any other financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding that no appeal has been filed by a tax authority pursuant to the orders or`
  line `instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1), it shall not be lawful for an assessee, being a party`
  line `in any appeal, to contend that the tax authority has acquiesced in the decision on the disputed issue by not`
  line `filing an appeal in any case.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal, hearing such appeal, shall have regard to the orders, instructions or`
  line `directions issued under sub-section (1) and the circumstances under which such appeal was filed or not`
  line `filed in respect of any case.`
  line
  line `(5) Every order, instruction or direction which has been issued by the Board fixing monetary limits`
  line `for filing an appeal shall be deemed to have been issued under sub-section (1) and the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32960)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Recovery of tax dues by Assessing Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32960&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any amount specified as payable in a notice of`
  line `demand under section 13 shall be paid within a period of thirty days of the service of the notice, to the`
  line `credit of the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Assessing Officer has any reason to believe that it will be detrimental to the interests of`
  line `revenue, if the period of thirty days referred to in sub-section (1) is allowed, he may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Joint Commissioner, reduce such period as he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Assessing Officer may, on an application made by the assessee, before the expiry of a period`
  line `of thirty days or the period reduced under sub-section (2) or during the pendency of appeal with the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals), extend the time for payment, or allow payment by instalments, subject to such`
  line `conditions as he may think fit to impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(4) An assessee shall be deemed to be an assessee in default, if the tax arrear is not paid within the`
  line `time allowed under sub-section (1) or the period reduced under sub-section (2) or extended under`
  line `sub-section (3), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an assessee defaults in paying any one of the instalments within the time fixed under`
  line `sub-section (3), he shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the whole of the then`
  line `outstanding amount.`
  line
  line `(6) The Assessing Officer may, in a case where no certificate has been drawn up under section 31 by`
  line `the Tax Recovery Officer, recover the amount in respect of which the assessee is in default, or is deemed`
  line `to be in default, by any one or more of the modes provided in section 32.`
  line
  line `(7) The Tax Recovery Officer shall be vested with the powers to recover the tax arrear on drawing up`
  line `of a statement of tax arrear under section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32961)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Recovery of tax dues by Tax Recovery Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32961&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tax Recovery Officer may draw up`
  line `under his signature a statement of tax arrears of an assessee referred to in sub-section (4) or`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 30, in such form, as may be prescribed (such statement hereafter in this Chapter`
  line `referred to as "certificate").`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate under sub-section (1) shall stand amended from time to time consequent to any`
  line `proceeding under this Act and the Tax Recovery Officer shall recover the amount so modified.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tax Recovery Officer may rectify any mistake apparent from the record.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tax Recovery Officer shall have the power to extend the time for payment, or allow payment`
  line `by instalments, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tax Recovery Officer shall proceed to recover from the assessee the amount specified in the`
  line `certificate by one or more of the modes referred to in section 32 or in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `(6) It shall not be open to the assessee to dispute the correctness of any certificate drawn up by the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer on any ground whatsoever, but it shall be lawful for the Tax Recovery Officer to`
  line `cancel the certificate if, for any reason, he thinks it necessary so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32962)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Modes of recovery of tax dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32962&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer may`
  line `require the employer of the assessee to deduct from any payment to the assessee such amount as is`
  line `sufficient to meet the tax arrear from the assessee.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon requisition under sub-section (1), the employer shall comply with the requisition and shall`
  line `pay the sum so deducted to the credit of the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any part of the salary, exempt from attachment in execution of a decree of a civil court under`
  line `section 60 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall be exempt from any requisition made`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer may, by notice in writing, require any debtor`
  line `of the assessee to pay such amount, not exceeding the amount of debt, as is sufficient to meet the tax`
  line `arrear of the assessee.`
  line
  line `(5) Upon receipt of the notice under sub-section (4), the debtor shall comply with the requisition and`
  line `shall pay the sum to the credit of the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed within the`
  line `time (not being before the debt becomes due to the assessee) specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(6) A copy of the notice issued under sub-section (4) shall be forwarded to the assessee at his last`
  line `address known to the Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer and in the case of a joint account, to`
  line `all the joint holders at their last addresses known to the Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(7) It shall not be necessary for any pass book, deposit receipt, policy or any other document to be`
  line `produced for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before payment is made,`
  line `notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary if the notice under sub-section (4) is`
  line `issued to a post office, banking company, insurer or any other person.`
  line
  line `(8) Any claim in respect of any property, in relation to which a notice under sub-section (4) has been`
  line `issued, arising after the date of the notice, shall be void as against any demand contained in the notice.`
  line
  line `(9) A person to whom a notice under sub-section (4) has been issued, shall not be required to pay the`
  line `amount of tax arrear specified therein, or part thereof, if he objects to it by a statement on oath that the`
  line `sum demanded, or any part thereof, is not due to the assessee or that he does not hold any money for, or`
  line `on account of, the assessee.`
  line
  line `(10) The person referred to in sub-section (9) shall be personally liable to the Assessing Officer or the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer, as the case may be, to the extent of his own liability to the assessee on the date of`
  line `the notice, or to the extent of the liability of the assessee for any sum due under this Act, whichever is`
  line `less, if it is discovered that the statement made by him was false in any respect.`
  line
  line `(11) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer may amend or revoke any notice issued`
  line `under sub-section (4) or extend the time for making any payment in pursuance of such notice.`
  line
  line `(12) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer shall grant a receipt for any amount paid in`
  line `compliance with a notice issued under sub-section (4), and the person so paying shall be fully discharged`
  line `from his liability to the assessee to the extent of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(13) Any person discharging any liability to the assessee after receipt of a notice under sub-section (4)`
  line `shall be personally liable to the Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer to the extent of his own`
  line `liability to the assessee so discharged or to the extent of the liability of the assessee for any sum due under`
  line `this Act, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(14) The debtor to whom a notice under sub-section (4) is sent shall be deemed to be an assessee in`
  line `default, if he fails to make such payment and further proceedings may be initiated against him for the`
  line `realisation of the amount in the manner provided in this section and the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `(15) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer may apply to the court, in whose custody`
  line `there is money belonging to the assessee, for payment to him of the entire amount of such money or if it`
  line `is more than the tax arrear, an amount sufficient to meet the tax arrear.`
  line
  line `(16) The Assessing Officer or the Tax Recovery Officer shall effect the recovery of any tax arrear in`
  line `the same manner as attachment, distraint and sale of any movable property under the Second Schedule to`
  line `the Income-tax Act, if he is so authorised by the Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, or the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner, by general or special order.`
  line
  line `(17) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) ''debtor'', in relation to an assessee, means,—`
  line
  line `(i) any person from whom any money is due, or may become due, to the assessee; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who holds, or may subsequently hold, any money for, or on account of, the`
  line `assessee; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any person who holds, or may subsequently hold, any money for, or on account of, the`
  line `assessee jointly with any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) shares of the joint holders in the account shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, to be`
  line equal.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32963)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Tax Recovery Officer by whom recovery of tax dues is to be effected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32963&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer competent to take action under section 31 shall be the Tax Recovery Officer —`
  line
  line `(a) within whose jurisdiction —`
  line
  line `(i) the assessee carries on his business;`
  line
  line `(ii) the principal place of business of the assessee is situate;`
  line
  line `(iii) the assessee resides; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any movable or immovable property of the assessee is situate; or`
  line
  line `(b) who has been assigned jurisdiction under section 6.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tax Recovery Officer, referred to in sub-section (1), may send a certificate, in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed, specifying the tax arrear to be recovered, to another Tax Recovery Officer within`
  line `whose jurisdiction the assessee resides or has property, if the first-mentioned Tax Recovery Officer —`
  line
  line `(a) is not able to recover the entire amount by sale of the property, movable or immovable, within`
  line `his jurisdiction; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of the opinion that, for the purpose of expediting, or securing, the recovery of the whole, or`
  line `any part, of the amount under this Chapter, it is necessary to send such certificate.`
  line
  line `(3) The second-mentioned Tax Recovery Officer shall, on receipt of the certificate, assume`
  line `jurisdiction for recovery of the amount of tax arrear specified therein and proceed to recover the amount`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32964)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Recovery of tax dues in case of a company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32964&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liquidator shall inform the`
  line `Assessing Officer, who has jurisdiction to assess the undisclosed foreign income and asset of the`
  line `company, of his appointment within a period of thirty days of his becoming the liquidator.`
  line
  line `(2) The Assessing Officer shall, within a period of three months from the date on which he receives`
  line `the information, intimate to the liquidator the amount which, in his opinion, would be sufficient to`
  line `provide for any tax arrears or any amount which is likely to become payable thereafter, by the company`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The liquidator—`
  line
  line `(a) shall not part with any of the assets of the company, or the properties, in his custody until he`
  line `has been intimated by the Assessing Officer under sub-section (2); and`
  line
  line `(b) on being so intimated, shall set aside an amount equal to the amount intimated.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon receipt of the intimation from the Assessing Officer under sub-section (2), the amount so`
  line `intimated shall, notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force, be the first charge`
  line `on the assets of the company remaining after payment of the following dues, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) workmen's dues; and`
  line
  line `(b) debts due to secured creditors to the extent such debts under clause (iii) of the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 325 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) are pari passu with such`
  line dues.
  line
  line `(5) The liquidator shall be personally liable for the payment of the amount payable by the company, if`
  line he—
  line
  line `(a) fails to inform in accordance with sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to set aside the amount as required by sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) The obligations and liabilities attached to the liquidator under this section shall attach to all the`
  line `liquidators jointly and severally in a case where there is more than one liquidator.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section shall prevail over anything to the contrary contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(8) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "liquidator" in relation to a company which is being wound up, whether under the orders of a`
  line `court or otherwise, shall include a receiver of the assets of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) "workmen's dues" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 325 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32965)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Liability of manager of a company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32965&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person being a manager at any time during the`
  line `financial year shall be jointly and severally liable for the payment of any amount due under this Act in`
  line `respect of the company for the financial year, if the amount cannot be recovered from the company.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply, if the manager proves that non-recovery cannot`
  line `be attributed to any neglect, misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall prevail over anything to the contrary contained in the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).`
  line
  line `(4) In this section, "manager" shall include a managing director and both shall have the meaning`
  line `respectively assigned to them in clause (53) and clause (54) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32966)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Joint and several liability of participants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32966&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, being a participant in an`
  line `unincorporated body at any time during the financial year, or the representative assessee of the deceased`
  line `participant, shall be jointly and severally liable, along with the unincorporated body, for payment of any`
  line `amount payable by the unincorporated body under this Act and all the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) In case of a limited liability partnership, the provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply, if the`
  line `partner proves that non-recovery cannot be attributed to any neglect, misfeasance or breach of duty on his`
  line `part in relation to the affairs of the partnership.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall prevail over anything to the contrary contained in the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32967)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Recovery through State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32967&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If the recovery of tax in any area has been entrusted to`
  line `a State Government under clause (1) of article 258 of the Constitution, the State Government may direct,`
  line `with respect to that area or any part thereof, that tax shall be recovered therein with, and as an addition to,`
  line `any municipal tax or local rate, by the same person and in the manner as the municipal tax or local rate is`
  line recovered.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32968)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Recovery of tax dues in pursuance of agreements with foreign countries or specified territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32968&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tax Recovery Officer may, in a case where an assessee has property in a country or a`
  line `specified territory outside India, forward a certificate to the Board for recovery of the tax arrears from the`
  line `assessee, where the Central Government or any specified association in India has entered into an`
  line `agreement with that country or territory under section 90 or section 90A of the Income-tax Act or under`
  line `sub-sections (1), (2) or sub-section (4) of section 73 of this Act, as the case may be, for the purposes of`
  line `recovery of tax.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the certificate under sub-section (3) from the Tax Recovery Officer, the Board may`
  line `take such action thereon as it may deem appropriate having regard to the terms of the agreement with`
  line `such country or a specified territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32969)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Recovery by suit or under other law not affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32969&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The several modes of recovery`
  line `specified in this Chapter shall not affect in anyway—`
  line
  line `(a) any other law for the time being in force relating to the recovery of debts due to the`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) the right of the Government to institute a suit for the recovery of the tax arrears from the`
  line assessee.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be lawful for the Assessing Officer, or the Government, to have recourse to any such law`
  line `or suit, notwithstanding that the tax arrears are being recovered from the assessee by any mode specified`
  line `in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32970)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Interest for default in furnishing return and payment or deferment of advance tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32970&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where the assessee has any income from a source outside India which has not been disclosed in the return`
  line `of income furnished under sub-section (1) of section 139of the Income-tax Act or the return of income`
  line `has not been furnished under the said sub-section, interest shall be chargeable in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 234A of the Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the assessee has any undisclosed income from a source outside India and the advance tax`
  line `on such income has not been paid in accordance with Part C of Chapter XVII of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `interest shall be chargeable in accordance with the provisions of sections 234B and 234C of the`
  line `Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32971)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Penalty in relation to undisclosed foreign income and asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32971&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The Assessing Officer may`
  line `direct that in a case where tax has been computed under section 10 in respect of undisclosed foreign`
  line `income and asset, the assessee shall pay by way of penalty, in addition to tax, if any, payable by him, a`
  line `sum equal to three times the tax computed under that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (32972)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish return in relation to foreign income and asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 164, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32972&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If a person, being a resident other than not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of clause (6) of section 6 of the Income-tax Act, who is required to furnish a return of his income for any previous year, as required under sub-section (1) of section 139 of the Income-tax Act or by the provisos to that sub-section, and who at any time during such previous year,--`
  line
  line `(i) held any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India as a beneficial owner or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(ii) was a beneficiary of any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) had any income from a source located outside India,`
  line
  line `and fails to furnish such return before the end of the relevant assessment year, the Assessing Officer may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that this section shall not apply in respect of an asset or assets (other than immovable property) where the aggregate value of such asset or assets does not exceed twenty lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For determining the value equivalent in rupees of the balance in an account maintained in foreign currency, the rate of exchange for calculation of the value in rupees shall be the telegraphic transfer buying rate of such currency as on the date for which the value is to be determined as adopted by the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (32973)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish in return of income, an information or furnish inaccurate particulars about an asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 164, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32973&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being a resident other than not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of clause (6) of section 6 of the Income-tax Act, who has furnished the return of income for any previous year under sub-section (1) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) of section 139 of the said Act, fails to furnish any information or furnishes inaccurate particulars in such return relating to any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India, held by him as a beneficial owner or otherwise, or in respect of which he was a beneficiary, or relating to any income from a source located outside India, at any time during such previous year, the Assessing Officer may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that this section shall not apply in respect of an asset or assets (other than immovable property), where the aggregate value of such asset or assets does not exceed twenty lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.The value equivalent in rupees shall be determined in the manner provided in the`
  line `Explanation to section 42.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (32974)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for default in payment of tax arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32974&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who is an assessee in default,`
  line `or an assessee deemed to be in default, as the case may be, in making payment of tax, and in case of`
  line `continuing default by such assessee, he shall be liable to a penalty of an amount, equal to the amount of`
  line `tax arrear.`
  line
  line `(2) An assessee shall not cease to be liable to any penalty under sub-section (1) merely by reason of`
  line `the fact that before the levy of such penalty he has paid the tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (32975)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for other defaults.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32975&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be liable to a penalty if he has, without`
  line `reasonable cause, failed to—`
  line
  line `(a) answer any question put to him by a tax authority in the exercise of its power sunder this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) sign any statement made by him in the course of any proceedings under this Act which a tax`
  line `authority may legally require him to sign;`
  line
  line `(c) attend or produce books of account or documents at the place or time, if he is required to`
  line `attend or to give evidence or produce books of account or other documents, at certain place and time`
  line `in response to summons issued under section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) The penalty referred to in sub-section (1) shall be a sum which shall not be less than fifty thousand`
  line `rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (32976)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title Procedure.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 219 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32976&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tax authority shall, for the purposes of imposing any penalty under this`
  line `Chapter, issue a notice to an assessee requiring him to show cause why the penalty should not be imposed`
  line `on him.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice referred to in sub-section (1) shall be issued—`
  line
  line `(a) during the pendency of any proceedings under this Act for the relevant previous year, in`
  line `respect of penalty referred to in section 41;`
  line
  line `(b) within a period of three years from the end of the financial year in which the default is`
  line `committed, in respect of penalties referred to in section 45.`
  line
  line `(3) No order imposing a penalty under this Chapter shall be made unless the assessee has been given`
  line `an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) An order imposing a penalty under this Chapter shall be made with the approval of the Joint`
  line `Commissioner, ^1`
  line `[or the Joint Director] if—`
  line
  line `(a) the penalty exceeds one lakh rupees and the tax authority levying the penalty is in the rank of`
  line `Income-tax Officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) the penalty exceeds five lakh rupees and the tax authority levying the penalty is in the rank of`
  line `Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner ^1`
  line `[or Assistant Director or Deputy Director].`
  line
  line `(5) Every order of penalty issued under this Chapter shall be accompanied by a notice of demand in`
  line `respect of the amount of penalty imposed and such notice of demand shall be deemed to be a notice under`
  line `section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (32977)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Bar of limitation for imposing penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32977&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order imposing a penalty under this Chapter`
  line `shall be passed after the expiry of a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which the`
  line `notice for imposition of penalty is issued under section 46.`
  line
  line `(2) An order imposing, or dropping the proceedings for imposition of, penalty under this Chapter may`
  line `be revised, or revived, as the case may be, on the basis of assessment of the undisclosed foreign income`
  line `and asset as revised after giving effect to the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, the High Court or the Supreme Court or order of revision under section 23 or section 24.`
  line
  line `(3) An order revising or reviving the penalty under sub-section (2) shall not be passed after the expiry`
  line `of a period of six months from the end of the month in which order of the Commissioner (Appeals), the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, the High Court or the Supreme Court is received by the Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner or the`
  line `order of revision under section 23 or section 24 is passed.`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, the following time or period`
  line `shall not be included—`
  line
  line `(a) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under section 7; and`
  line
  line `(b) any period during which a proceeding under this Chapter for the levy of penalty is stayed by`
  line `an order, or injunction, of any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (32978)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Chapter not in derogation of any other law or any other provision of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32978&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `provisions of this Chapter shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law`
  line `providing for prosecution for offences there under.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Chapter shall be independent of any order under this Act that may be made,`
  line `or has not been made, on any person and it shall be no defence that the order has not been made on`
  line `account of time limitation or for any other reason.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (32979)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Punishment for failure to furnish return in relation to foreign income and asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32979&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `If a`
  line `person, being a resident other than not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of clause (6) of`
  line `section 6 of the Income-tax Act, who at any time during the previous year, held any asset (including`
  line `financial interest in any entity) located outside India as a beneficial owner or otherwise, or was a`
  line `beneficiary of such asset or had income from a source outside India and wilfully fails to furnish in due`
  line `time the return of income which he is required to furnish under sub-section (1) of section 139 of that Act,`
  line `he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but`
  line `which may extend to seven years and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be proceeded against under this section for failure to furnish in due`
  line `time the return of income under sub-section (1) of section 139 of the Income-tax Act if the return is`
  line `furnished by him before the expiry of the assessment year.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (32980)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Punishment for failure to furnish in return of income, any information about an asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32980&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being a resident other`
  line `than not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of clause (6) of section 6 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `who has furnished the return of income for any previous year under sub-section (1) or sub-section (4) or`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 139 of that Act, wilfully fails to furnish in such return any information relating`
  line `to anasset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India, held by him, as a beneficial`
  line `owner or otherwise or in which he was a beneficiary, at any time during such previous year, or disclose`
  line `any income from a source outside India, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (32981)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Punishment for wilful attempt to evade tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32981&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person, being a resident other than not`
  line `ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of clause (6) of section 6 of the Income-tax Act, wilfully`
  line `attempts in any manner whatsoever to evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under`
  line `this Act, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `years but which may extend to ten years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person wilfuly attempts in any manner whatsoever to evade the payment of any tax, penalty or`
  line `interest under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that maybe imposable on him under any`
  line `other provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than three months but which may extend to three years and shall, in the discretion of the court, also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable`
  line `or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof shall include a case where any person—`
  line
  line `(i) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents(being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes or causes to be made any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) wilfuly omits or causes to be omitted any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents; or`
  line
  line `(iv) causes any other circumstance to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (32982)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Punishment for false statement in verification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32982&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If a person, makes a statement in any`
  line `verification under this Act or under any rule made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which`
  line `is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (32983)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Punishment for abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32983&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to make`
  line `and deliver an account or a statement or declaration relating to tax payable under this Act which is false`
  line `and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true or to commit an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 51, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (32984)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Presumption as to culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32984&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any prosecution for any offence under this Act`
  line `which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the existence of`
  line `such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no such mental`
  line `state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive or knowledge of`
  line `a fact or belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (32985)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Prosecution to be at instance of Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or Principal Commissioner or Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32985&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `55. ^1`
  line `[Prosecution to be at instance of Principal Chief Commissioner or Principal Director`
  line `General or Chief Commissioner or Director General or Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner].—(1) A person shall not be proceeded against for an offence under section 49 to section`
  line `53 (both inclusive) except with the sanction of the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner ^2`
  line `[or the Principal Director General`
  line `or the Director General] may issue such instructions, or directions, to the tax authorities referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) as he may think fit for the institution of proceedings under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The power of the Board to issue orders, instructions or directions under this Act shall include the`
  line `power to issue orders, instructions or directions (including instructions or directions to obtain its previous`
  line `approval) to other tax authorities for the proper initiation of proceedings of offences (including an`
  line `authorisation to file and pursue complaints by one or more Inspectors of tax) under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 219, for "Prosecution to be at instance of Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Principal Commissioner or Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 219, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (32986)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32986&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall render any such person liable to any punishment if he proves that`
  line `the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the`
  line `commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been committed`
  line `by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or`
  line `is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a person, being a company, and the`
  line `punishment for such offence is imprisonment and fine, then, without prejudice to sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (3), such company shall be punished with fine and every person, referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `or the director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company referred to in sub-section (3), shall be`
  line `liable to be proceeded against and punished in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) In this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes —`
  line
  line `(i) an unincorporated body;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Hindu undivided family;`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to —`
  line
  line `(i) an unincorporated body, means a participant in the body;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Hindu undivided family, means an adult member of the family; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a company, means a whole-time director, or where there is no such director, any other`
  line `director or manager or officer, who is in charge of the affairs of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (32987)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Proof of entries in records of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32987&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The entries in the records, or other documents,`
  line `in the custody of a tax authority shall be admitted in evidence in any proceeding for the prosecution of`
  line `any person for an offence under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The entries referred to in sub-section (1) may be proved by the production of—`
  line
  line `(a) the records or other documents (containing such entries) in the custody of the tax authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the entries certified by that authority under its signature, as true copy of the original`
  line `entries contained in the records or other documents in its custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (32988)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Punishment for second and subsequent offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32988&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `If any person convicted of an offence under`
  line `section 49 to section 53 (both inclusive)is again convicted of an offence under any of the aforesaid`
  line `provisions, he shall be punishable for the second and every subsequent offence with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years, but which may extend to ten years and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees, but which may extend to one crore rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (32989)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Declaration of undisclosed foreign asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32989&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, any person`
  line `may make, on or after the date of commencement of this Act but on or before a date to be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in the Official Gazette, a declaration in respect of any undisclosed asset located`
  line `outside India and acquired from income chargeable to tax under the Income-tax Act for any assessment`
  line `year prior to the assessment year beginning on 1st day of April, 2016—`
  line
  line `(a) for which he has failed to furnish a return under section 139 of the Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(b) which he has failed to disclose in a return of income furnished by him under the Income-tax`
  line `Act before the date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) which has escaped assessment by reason of the omission or failure on the part of such person`
  line `to make a return under the Income-tax Act or to disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary`
  line `for the assessment or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (32990)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Charge of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32990&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act or in any Finance`
  line `Act, the undisclosed asset located outside India and declared under section 59 within the time specified`
  line `therein shall be chargeable to tax at the rate of thirty per cent. of value of such undisclosed asset on the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (32991)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32991&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act or in any Finance Act, the`
  line `person making a declaration of undisclosed asset located outside India shall, in addition to tax charged`
  line `under section 60, be liable to penalty at the rate of one hundred per cent. of such tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (32992)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Manner of declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32992&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) A declaration under section 59 shall be made to the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or the Commissioner and shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line `(2) The declaration shall be signed,—`
  line
  line `(i) where the declarant is an individual, by the individual himself; where such individual is absent`
  line `from India, by the individual concerned or by some person duly authorised by him in this behalf; and`
  line `where the individual is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by his guardian or by any`
  line `other person competent to act on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the declarant is a Hindu undivided family, by the karta, and where the karta is absent`
  line `from India or is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by any other adult member of`
  line `such family;`
  line
  line `(iii) where the declarant is a company, by the managing director thereof, or where for any`
  line `unavoidable reason such managing director is not able to sign th edeclaration or where there is no`
  line `managing director, by any director thereof;`
  line
  line `(iv) where the declarant is a firm, by the managing partner thereof, or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing partner is not able to sign the declaration, or where there is no managing`
  line `partner as such, by any partner thereof, not being a minor;`
  line
  line `(v) where the declarant is any other association, by any member of the association or the principal`
  line `officer thereof; and`
  line
  line `(vi) where the declarant is any other person, by that person or by some other person competent to`
  line `act on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person, who has made a declaration under sub-section (1) in respect of his asset or as a`
  line `representative assessee in respect of the asset of any other person, shall not been titled to make any other`
  line `declaration, under that sub-section in respect of his asset or the asset of such other person, and any such`
  line `other declaration, if made, shall be deemed to be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (32993)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Time for payment of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32993&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tax payable under section 60 and penalty payable under`
  line `section 61 in respect of the undisclosed asset located outside India, shall be paid on or before a date to be`
  line `notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The declarant shall file the proof of payment of tax and penalty on or before the date notified`
  line `under sub-section (1), with the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner before whom the`
  line `declaration under section 59 was made.`
  line
  line `(3) If the declarant fails to pay the tax in respect of the declaration made under section59 on or before`
  line `the date notified under sub-section (1), the declaration filed by him shall be deemed never to have been`
  line `made under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (32994)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Undisclosed foreign asset declared not to be included in total income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32994&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The amount of`
  line `undisclosed investment in an asset located outside India declared in accordance with section 59 shall not`
  line `be included in the total income of the declarant for any assessment year under the Income-tax Act, if the`
  line `declarant makes the payment of tax referred to in section 60 and the penalty referred to in section 61 by`
  line `the date notified under sub-section (1) of section 63.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (32995)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Undisclosed foreign asset declared not to affect finality of completed assessments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32995&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line The
  line `declarant shall not be entitled, in respect of undisclosed asset located outside India declared or any`
  line `amount of tax paid thereon, to reopen any assessment or reassessment made under the Income-tax Act or`
  line `the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957) or claim any set off or relief in any appeal, reference or other`
  line `proceeding in relation to any such assessment or reassessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (32996)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Tax in respect of voluntarily disclosed asset not refundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32996&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Any amount of tax paid under`
  line `section 60 or penalty paid under section 61 in pursuance of a declaration made under section 59 shall not`
  line `be refundable.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (32997)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Declaration not admissible in evidence against declarant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32997&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, nothing contained in any declaration made under`
  line `section 59 shall be admissible in evidence against the declarant for the purpose of any proceeding relating`
  line `to imposition of penalty, other than the penalty leviable under section 61, or for the purposes of`
  line `prosecution under the Income-tax Act or the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957) or the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act,1999 (42 of 1999) or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or the Customs Act, 1962`
  line `(52 of 1962) .`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (32998)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Declaration by misrepresentation of facts to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32998&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Chapter, where a declaration has been made by misrepresentation or suppression of facts, such`
  line `declaration shall be void and shall be deemed never to have been made under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (32999)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Exemption from wealth-tax in respect of assets specified in declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=32999&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `undisclosed asset located outside India is represented by cash(including bank deposits), bullion or any`
  line `other assets specified in the declaration made under section 59—`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of which the declarant has failed to furnish a return under section14 of the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957) for the assessment year commencing on or before the1st day of`
  line `April, 2015; or`
  line
  line `(b) which have not been shown in the return of net wealth furnished by him for the said`
  line `assessment year or years; or`
  line
  line `(c) which have been understated in value in the return of net wealth furnished by him for the said`
  line `assessment year or years, then, notwithstanding anything contained in the Wealth-tax Act, 1957`
  line `(27 of 1957) or any rules made thereunder,—`
  line
  line `(I) wealth-tax shall not be payable by the declarant in respect of the assets referred to in clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b) and such assets shall not be included in his net wealth for the said assessment year or years;`
  line
  line `(II) the amount by which the value of the assets referred to in clause (c) has been understated in the`
  line `return of net wealth for the said assessment year or years, to the extent such amount does not exceed the`
  line `voluntarily disclosed income utilised for acquiring such assets, shall not be taken into account in`
  line `computing the net wealth of the declarant for the said assessment year or years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where a declaration under section 59 is made by a firm, the assets referred to in`
  line `clause (I) or, as the case may be, the amount referred to in clause (II) shall not be taken into account in`
  line `computing the net wealth of any partner of the firm or, as the case may be, in determining the value of the`
  line `interest of any partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply unless the conditions specified in`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 63 are fulfilled by the declarant.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (33000)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Applicability of certain provisions of Income-tax Act and of Chapter V of Wealth-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33000&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Chapter XV of the Income-tax Act relating to liability in special cases and of section`
  line `189 of that Act or of Chapter V of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957)relating to liability to assessment`
  line `in special cases shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to proceeding sunder this Chapter as they apply`
  line `in relation to proceedings under the Income-tax Act or, as the case may be, the Wealth-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (33001)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Chapter not to apply to certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33001&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply—`
  line
  line `(a) to any person in respect of whom an order of detention has been made under the Conservation`
  line `of Foreign Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities Act, 1974 (52 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(i) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 or section 12A`
  line `of the said Act do not apply, has not been revoked on the report of the Advisory Board under`
  line `section 8 of the said Act or before the receipt of the report of the Advisory Board; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 of the said Act`
  line `apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the review under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 9, or on the report of the Advisory Board under section 8, read with`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9, of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 12A of the said`
  line `Act apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the first`
  line `review under sub-section (3) of that section, or on the basis of the report of the Advisory Board`
  line `under section 8, read with sub-section (6) of section 12A, of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iv) such order of detention has not been set aside by a court of competent jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to prosecution for any offence punishable under Chapter IX or Chapter XVII of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985`
  line `(61 of 1985), the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967 (37 of 1967), the Prevention of`
  line `Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988);`
  line
  line `(c) to any person notified under section 3 of the Special Court (Trial of Offences Relating to`
  line `Transactions in Securities) Act, 1992 (27 of 1992).`
  line
  line `(d) in relation to any undisclosed asset located outside India which has been acquired from`
  line `income chargeable to tax under the Income-tax Act for any previous year relevant to an assessment`
  line `year prior to the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2016—`
  line
  line `(i) where a notice under section 142 or sub-section (2) of section 143 or section 148 or`
  line `section 153A or section 153C of the Income-tax Act has been issued in respect of such`
  line `assessment year and the proceeding is pending before the Assessing Officer; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where a search has been conducted under section 132 or requisition has been made under`
  line `section 132A or a survey has been carried out under section 133A of the Income-tax Act in a`
  line `previous year and a notice under sub-section(2) of section 143 for the assessment year relevant to`
  line `such previous year or a notice under section 153A or under section 153C of the said Act for an`
  line `assessment year relevant to any previous year prior to such previous year has not been issued and`
  line `the time for issuance of such notice has not expired; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where any information has been received by the competent authority under an agreement`
  line `entered into by the Central Government under section 90 or section 90A of the Income-tax Act in`
  line `respect of such undisclosed asset.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this sub-clause asset shall include a bank account whether`
  line `having any balance or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (33002)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Removal of doubts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33002&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that—`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in the Explanation to sub-section (1)of section 69,`
  line `nothing contained in this Chapter shall be construed as conferring any benefit, concession or`
  line `immunity on any person other than the person making the declaration under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) where any declaration has been made under section 59 but no tax and penalty has been paid`
  line `within the time specified under section 60 and section 61, the value of such asset shall be chargeable`
  line `to tax under this Act in the previous year in which such declaration is made;`
  line
  line `(c) where any asset has been acquired or made prior to commencement of this Act, and no`
  line `declaration in respect of such asset is made under this Chapter, such asset shall be deemed to have`
  line `been acquired or made in the year in which a notice under section 10 is issued by the Assessing Officer and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (33003)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Agreement with foreign countries or specified territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33003&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may`
  line `enter into an agreement with the Government of any other country—`
  line
  line `(a) for exchange of information for the prevention of evasion or avoidance of tax on undisclosed`
  line `foreign income chargeable under this Act or under the corresponding law in force in that country, or`
  line `investigation of cases of such evasion or avoidance;`
  line
  line `(b) for recovery of tax under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that country.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may enter into an agreement with the Government of any specified`
  line `territory outside India for the purposes specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, make such provisions as may be necessary for`
  line `implementing the agreements referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Any specified association in India may enter into an agreement with any specified association in`
  line `the specified territory outside India for the purposes of sub-section (1) and the Central Government may`
  line `by notification make such provisions as may be necessary for adopting and implementing such`
  line agreement.
  line
  line `(5) Any term used but not defined in this Act or in the agreement referred to in sub-sections (1), (2) or`
  line `sub-section (4) shall, unless the context otherwise requires, and is not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act or the agreement, have the meaning assigned to it in the notification issued by the Central`
  line `Government and such meaning shall be deemed to have effect from the date on which the said agreement`
  line `came into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (33004)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Service of notice generally.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33004&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) The service of any notice, summons, requisition, order or any`
  line `other communication under this Act (herein referred to in this section as "communication") may be made`
  line `by delivering or transmitting a copy thereof, to the person named therein,—`
  line
  line `(a) by post or by such courier service as may be approved by the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) in such manner as provided under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the`
  line `purposes of service of summons;`
  line
  line `(c) in the form of any electronic record as provided in Chapter IV of the Information Technology`
  line `Act, 2000 (21 of 2000); or`
  line
  line `(d) by any other means of transmission of documents, including fax message or electronic mail`
  line `message, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may make rules providing for the addresses including the address for electronic mail or`
  line `electronic mail message to which the communication referred to in sub-section (1) may be delivered or`
  line `transmitted to the person named therein.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the expressions "electronic mail" and "electronic mail message" shall have the`
  line `same meanings as assigned to them in the Explanation to section 66A of the Information Technology`
  line `Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (33005)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Authentication of notices and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33005&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) A notice or any other document required`
  line `to be issued, served or given for the purposes of this Act by any tax authority shall be authenticated by`
  line `that authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notice or other document to be issued, served or given for the purposes of this Act by any`
  line `tax authority shall be deemed to be authenticated, if the name and office of a designated tax authority is`
  line `printed, stamped or otherwise written thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, a designated tax authority shall mean any tax authority authorized by the Board to`
  line `issue, serve or give such notice or other document after authentication in the manner as provided in`
  line `sub-section (2)@i/@.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (33006)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Notice deemed to be valid in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33006&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) A notice which is required to be`
  line `served upon a person for the purposes of assessment under this Act shall be deemed to have been duly`
  line `served upon him in accordance with the provisions of this Act, if the person has appeared in any`
  line `proceeding or co-operated in any inquiry relating to an assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) The person, referred to in sub-section (1), shall be precluded from taking any objection in any`
  line `proceeding or inquiry under this Act that the notice was—`
  line
  line `(a) not served upon him;`
  line
  line `(b) not served upon him in time; or`
  line
  line `(c) served upon him in an improper manner.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall not apply, if the person has raised the objection before the`
  line `completion of the assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (33007)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Appearance by approved valuer in certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33007&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee who is entitled or`
  line `required to attend before any tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal, in connection with any matter`
  line `relating to the valuation of any asset, may attend through a valuer approved by the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or the Commissioner in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in a case where the assessee is required to attend`
  line `personally for examination on oath or affirmation under section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (33008)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Appearance by authorised representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33008&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee who is entitled or required to`
  line `attend before any tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal, in connection with any proceeding under this`
  line `Act, may attend through an authorised representative.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply in a case where the assessee is required to attend`
  line `personally for examination on oath or affirmation under section 8.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, "authorised representative" means a person authorised by the assessee in writing to`
  line `appear on his behalf, being—`
  line
  line `(a) a person related to the assessee in any manner, or a person regularly employed by the`
  line assessee;
  line
  line `(b) any officer of a scheduled bank with which the assessee maintains a current account or has`
  line `other regular dealings;`
  line
  line `(c) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practice in any civil court in India;`
  line
  line `(d) an accountant;`
  line
  line `(e) any person who has passed any accountancy examination recognised in this behalf by the`
  line `Board; or`
  line
  line `(f) any person who has acquired such educational qualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The following persons shall not be qualified to represent an assessee under sub-section (1),`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been dismissed or removed from Government service;`
  line
  line `(b) a legal practitioner, or an accountant, who is found guilty of misconduct in his professional`
  line `capacity by any authority entitled to institute disciplinary proceedings against him;`
  line
  line `(c) a person, not being a legal practitioner or an accountant, who is found guilty of misconduct in`
  line `any tax proceedings by such authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner may, by an order in writing,`
  line `specify the period upto which the disqualification under sub-section (4) shall continue, having regard to`
  line `the nature of misconduct and such disqualification shall not exceed—`
  line
  line `(i) in case of clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (4), a period of ten years;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of clause (b) of sub-section (4), the period for which the legal practitioner or an`
  line `accountant is not entitled to practice.`
  line
  line `(6) A person shall not be allowed to appear as an authorised representative, if he has committed any`
  line `fraud or misrepresented the facts which resulted in loss to the revenue and that person has been declared`
  line `as such by an order of the Principal Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) who holds a valid`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (33009)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Rounding off of income, value of asset and tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33009&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of undisclosed foreign`
  line `income and asset computed in accordance with this Act shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of one`
  line `hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount payable or receivable by the assessee under this Act shall be rounded off to the`
  line `nearest multiple of ten rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) The method of rounding off under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (33010)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Congnizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33010&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a metropolitan magistrate or a magistrate`
  line `of the First Class shall try any offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (33011)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Assessment not to be invalid on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33011&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `No assessment, notice, summons or other`
  line `proceedings, made or issued or taken or purported to have been made or issued or taken in pursuance of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act shall be invalid or shall be deemed to be invalid merely by reason of any`
  line `mistake, defector omission in such assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding if such assessment,`
  line `notice, summons or other proceeding is in substance and effect in conformity with or according to the`
  line `intent and purpose of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (33012)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Bar of suits in civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33012&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit shall be brought in any civil court to set aside or modify`
  line `any proceeding taken or order made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No prosecution, suit or other proceeding shall lie against the Government or any officer of the`
  line `Government, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done, under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (33013)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Income-tax papers to be available for purposes of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33013&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Income-tax Act, all information contained in any statement or return made or furnished`
  line `under the provisions of that Act or obtained or collected for the purposes of the said Act may be used for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (33014)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Application of provisions of Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33014&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of clauses (c) and (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 90, clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (1) of section 90A, sections 119, 133, 134,`
  line `135, 138, Chapter XV and sections 237, 240, 245, 280, 280A, 280B, 280D, 281, 281B and 284 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act shall apply with necessary modifications as if the said provisions refer to undisclosed`
  line `foreign income and asset instead of to income-tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (33015)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33015&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, subject to the approval of the Central Government,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of determination of the value of an undisclosed foreign as setreferred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the tax authority to be prescribed for any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner of service of a notice of demand under section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which any appeal, revision or cross-objection may be filed under this Act, the`
  line `manner in which they may be verified and the fee payable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which the Tax Recovery Officer may draw up the statement of tax arrears under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the sum is to be paid to the credit of Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (5) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the Tax Recovery Officer shall send a certificate referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which a declaration referred to in sub-section (1) of section 62 is to be made and`
  line `the manner in which it is to be verified;`
  line
  line `(i) the means of transmission of documents under clause (d) of sub-section (1)of section 74;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure for approval of a valuer by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner`
  line `under section 77;`
  line
  line `(k) the educational qualifications required, to be an authorised representative under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(l) the tax authority under clause (c) of sub-section (4) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(m) the method of rounding off of the amount referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 79;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which by this Act is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act and`
  line `no retrospective effect shall be given to any rule so as to prejudicially affect the interest of assessees.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this Act to be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (33016)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33016&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on`
  line `which the provisions of this Act come into force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (33017)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Amendment of section 2 of Act 54 of 1963.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33017&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `In section 2 of the Central Boards of Revenue`
  line `Act, 1963, in sub-clause (1) of clause (c),—`
  line
  line `(a) in item (vii), the word "and" occurring at the end shall be omitted; and`
  line
  line `(b) after item (ix) as so amended, the following item shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(x) the Black Money (Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets) and Imposition of Tax`
  line `Act, 2015; and"`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (33018)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Amendment of Act of 15 of 2003.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155&sectionId=33018&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00045_201522_1517807328155
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `In the Prevention of Money-laundering Act, 2002, in the`
  line `Schedule, in Part C, after entry (3), relating to the offences against property under Chapter XVII of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(4) The offence of wilful attempt to evade any tax, penalty or interest referred to in section 51 of the`
  line `Black Money (Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets) and Imposition of Tax Act, 2015.".`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
